SIMPLE: usurper
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Usurper
<hw>U*surp"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who usurps;
especially, one who seizes illegally on sovereign power; <as>as, the
<ex>usurper</ex> of a throne, of power, or of the rights of a
patron</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A crown will not want pretenders to claim it, not
<qex>usurpers</qex>, if their power serves them, to possess it.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Usurpingly</ent>⟦br⟧
